The RAdial Velocity Experiment (RAVE) provides precise radial velocities and stellar atmosphere parameters for 483,849 objects using medium-resolution spectra (R = 7,500) in the Ca II-triplet region (8410 - 8795 \AA) \citep{2006AJ....132.1645S}. Using the fourth data release of the RAVE catalogue, RAVE--DR4 \citep{2013AJ....146..134K}, we apply the selection criteria developed in \citet{2015MNRAS.451.1229A} for data quality, where stars with a S/N $>$ 10, cross-correlation coefficient R larger than 5 and classification flag set to "n" were selected. From this sample, we further selected giant stars within the range 3600 K $<$ T$_{\rm eff}$ $<$ 6000 K, log $g$ $<$ 3.5 and [M/H] $<$ +0.0 dex. Most of the selected spectra have a S/N $>$ 20. These stars have a typical error in radial velocity $\leq$ 2 km s$^{-1}$. For this selection, we explore the radial velocity in the Galactic Standard of Rest frame (v$_{GSR}$) using the following formulae:

